<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-18T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-18T07:00:00-05:00" n="225" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10742</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-18T13:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 20, 3.16
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3997. My 3914, July 9.<note n="2" xml:id="d225fn2">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_283">p.
                                    283</ref>.</note> I learn that memorandum mentioned was later
                                submitted by my Bulgarian informant to British official, Geneva, who
                                is taking up with his Government the question of giving financial
                                support to Bulgarian Revolutionary Party. Efforts are also being
                                made to facilitate the journey to Switzerland of Bulgarian <pb facs="0383" n="291" xml:id="pg_291"/> Radical leader … to
                                ascertain his plans and possibility of such a revolutionary
                                movement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>